# Pre-push gate

When the user asks to **commit**, **push**, **deploy**, or **go live**:

1. Read and follow `.cursor/skills/pre-push-review/SKILL.md`
2. Run **ce-code-review** with `mode:report-only` on the current diff unless user already approved a full review
3. Output the Go-Live Readiness report and verdict (**✅ Production Push Safe** or **❌ Push Blocked**)
4. Do **not** run `git push` until verdict is safe or user explicitly overrides after seeing critical issues
5. After push to `publish-main`, remind: merge into **`main`** for Vercel production

For "why is it slow" questions, use the Performance analyzer section in the pre-push skill.
